            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.40.23" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">23</fw>
                <note type="curatorial">Aly Collection
                
                
                194-1</note>

                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                <hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT</hi>
                    <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">SKYRIM FARM</hi>
                    <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA, MISSOURI</hi>     
                </fw>
                <opener><dateline>June 25, 1963</dateline>
                
                <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Two weeks ago last Sunday, I was in an auto accident about forty miles north of Vermillion, South Dakota. I was in the hospital six days and then six more days in bed at the home of Dr. Christ. I reached here day before yesterday, and I am still pretty well bunged up, although I am sure I will be all right after some weeks. While the experience has been very painful, the kindness I have experienced has been worth the trouble. At the hospital in Viborg, South Dakota, it was as though I were a long-lost relative returned, and I heard from so many people, and many called on me. I am not sure about making the Oregon trip, but I am hoping.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Same old affection</salute>
                
                <signed>John</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note>J. N./gail</note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
